The paper proposes a new approach for dynamic taint analysis using neural program embeddings, which falls under the category of program analysis and security. Therefore, cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the efficiency and accuracy of the proposed approach, which involves machine learning techniques, making cs.SE (Software Engineering) another likely sub-category. The use of neural networks for program embeddings also suggests the possibility of the paper being categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves the use of programming languages and constructs, which could place it under cs.PL (Programming Languages). Finally, the use of saliency maps for influence analysis suggests the possibility of the paper being categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
